Citation.sTitle: Density, Viscosity, and Refractive Index for Water + 2-Butoxyethanol and + 2-(2-Butoxyethoxy)ethanol at Various Temperatures
Citation.sAbstract: Density, viscosity, and refractive index for the binary systems water + 2-butoxyethanol and water + 2-(2-butoxyethoxy)ethanol have been measured at the temperatures ranging from (283.15 to 323.15) K at atmospheric pressure. The excess molar volume and deviations of viscosity and refractive index from a mole fraction average of these binary mixtures were correlated by the Redlich-Kister equation.
